Name: Central Singapore
Description: The central region of Singapore, known for its business and financial districts, landmarks like Marina Bay Sands, and vibrant cultural hubs.

Name: North Singapore
Description: A region known for its residential communities, parks, and educational institutions. It includes areas such as Woodlands and Yishun.

Name: West Singapore
Description: A region that includes both residential and industrial areas, as well as nature reserves like Bukit Timah and Jurong Lake Gardens.

Name: East Singapore
Description: A region known for its coastal areas, recreational parks like East Coast Park, and iconic landmarks such as Changi Airport.

Name: Northeast Singapore
Description: A region known for its mix of residential areas, recreational facilities, and green spaces. It includes areas such as Sengkang and Punggol.
